HEADWORD: Rotalite
<hw>Ro"ta*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>rota</ets>
wheel + <ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>Any fossil
foraminifer of the genus <gen>Rotalia</gen>, abundant in the chalk
formation. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Rhizopod</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

